# Validating Input

## Length Check
```java
if (args.length < 1) {
    sender.sendMessage("Usage: /heal <player>");
    return true;
}
```

## Exact Length
```java
if (args.length != 1) {
    sender.sendMessage("Invalid usage");
}
```

## Logic
- Prevent errors
- Guide user

## Best Practice
Always validate before using args.

# Targeting Players

## Example
```java
Player target = Bukkit.getPlayer(args[0]);

if (target == null) {
    sender.sendMessage("Player not found");
    return true;
}

target.sendMessage("You were targeted!");
```

## Logic
- Convert string → player
- Check if exists

## Edge Case
Offline players return null.

# Parsing Numbers

## Example
```java
int amount;

try {
    amount = Integer.parseInt(args[0]);
} catch (NumberFormatException e) {
    sender.sendMessage("Must be a number!");
    return true;
}
```

## Logic
- Convert string → int
- Catch invalid input

## Edge Case
User enters text → crash if not handled.

# True/False Arguments

## Example
```java
boolean enabled = Boolean.parseBoolean(args[0]);

if (enabled) {
    sender.sendMessage("Enabled!");
} else {
    sender.sendMessage("Disabled!");
}
```

## Logic
- "true" → true
- Anything else → false

## Warning
"yes" or "1" = false
